05/04/2011
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- A court on Monday (April 4th) found three people guilty of stealing the body of former Cypriot President Tassos Papadopoulos from a Nicosia cemetery in December 2009.
Three months passed before police found his remains and arrested three suspects -- an Indian and two Cypriots, one of whom is already serving a life sentence in a Cypriot prison.
Sentencing will be on April 18th.
(Cyprus Mail, Famagusta Gazette, Xinhua - 05/04/11)
